File: President Cyril Ramaphosa. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa is set to unveil his much anticipated economic reconstruction and recovery plan. Ramaphosa will virtually address the two Houses of Parliament, these being the National Assembly and the National Council of Provinces. The president says the coronavirus pandemic has plunged the country and the continent into an unprecedented crisis. READ:Â Mboweni's request subject to parliamentary committee approval He says extraordinary measures are required to ensure a speedy and sustainable economic recovery. The recovery plan is the result of extensive deliberation between government and its social partners, including business and labour.